    2... Nf6
      ( 2... c6!? {is a trendy and strong antidote as well.} )
    3. Bg2 d5 {3...Bc5!? and 3...c6!? are also respectable.}
      ( 3... Bc5!? )
      ( 3... c6!? )
    4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. O-O {I have used this move order in my own
    correspondence games. Now 6...Nb6 would transpose to the main tabiya of
